1977. The Palestinian left regards Shaikh al-Qassam as a social rebel.

<P><A NAME="b3"></A>3. Sumud is an equivalent value used by the PLO to
encourage inhabitants in the Occupied Territories as a formula settling
the contradiction between the principle of armed struggle and quiet and
collaboration with the occupying authorities.

